PORT ELIZABETH, September 20  – There were scenes of celebration on Thursday at the Port Elizabeth High Court after it dismissed an application brought by the Democratic Alliance (DA) challenging the outcome of a controversial council meeting which saw the ousting of Athol Trollip as mayor. The United Democratic Movement’s (UDM) Mongameli Bobani is the legitimate mayor of Nelson Mandela Bay after the Democratic Alliance (DA) and its coalition partners, COPE and the ACDP, lost its application in the Port Elizabeth High Court. Court to hand down Judgment in Trollip ousting as Nelson Mandela Bay mayor  